title: Arsenal Ladies hit 10 against Spurs
text:
Arsenal Ladies hit 10 against Tottenham in Women's FA Cup Last Updated: 19/03/17 9:09pm Danielle van de Donk bagged a treble for Arsenal Holders Arsenal Ladies are through to the quarter-finals of the SSE Women's FA Cup after romping to a 10-0 victory over Tottenham at Meadow Park. 
Danielle van de Donk led the way for the hosts with a hat-trick, which included a superb back-heel from a Dan Carter cross. 
Carter herself netted twice and the other scorers included the former Sunderland striker Beth Mead, who found the net on her debut, Carter (2), Kim Little, Dominique Janssen, Chloe Kelly and Katie McCabe. The holders inflicted a double-figured defeat on their north London neighbours 
The goals were split evenly, with five in each half, and Van De Donk rounded off the scoring six minutes from full-time. 
Last year's beaten finalists Chelsea also cruised into the last eight, hammering Doncaster 7-0, and Shanice van de Sanden got the winner in extra time as Liverpool Ladies beat Everton 2-1. 
The quarter final draw will be held on Monday morning. Also See:
